CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 29, 1952, pg. 1 reads: "Happy Moments in Lives Of These "Favorite Churchwomen" - These five contestants shared honors last Thursday night in A. Leo Weil School Auditorium...The Rev. A. L .Salmon, in second picture, looks at the check for $50 that his contestant, Mrs. Susie Hollis, third prize winner, won for her church..."
TitMainTitle: Rev. A. L. Salmon and Susie Hollis, holding check, with Jessie Vann looking on, standing at podium on stage in A. Leo Weil school during "Favorite Churchwoman's" Contest award program
